Subject: Re: [T2] Why is it Knocking ?

Sounds like a lifter and I would consider pulling them and cleaning them.
Also I would consider readjusting them. The archives have the updated 
procedure and it is also a big deal on the Vanagon list and Boston Bob's 
website.

:
>Hello Everyone..  This is kind of long.. I have a 78 Westy ..Only gets 
>driven on weekends , and not everyone. I drove it back from Santa Cruz to 
>Santa Rosa and parked it for two weeks .. started it up and it was making 
>a ticking/ knocking noise. Turned it off and researched the list and 
>decided that it was a lifter. Changed the oil to a lighter grade and ran 
>it for 20 minutes and it stopped making a noise. Drove it for a week ,no 
>noise,  parked it on a hill side ways for 9 hours , got in, started it and 
>it started knocking really loud. drove it 2 miles to my brothers house and 
>then towed it home. started it up and drove in the garage.. Where it sits. 
>.Started it again , pulled each plug wire and it still made noise...Still 
>thinking it's a lifter.. pulled valve covers, pushed in the rocker arm 
>where it attaches to push rod.. all cylinders where hard except #4 .. I 
>can push in the push rod , on the intact and exhaust side. The question I 
>have is...Is this a soft lifter and will it make that kind of noise .. 
>Should I be checking other things....I really keep the maintenance up on 
>the Westy, never over heat it    Thanks in advance...

